# CODEOWNERS — two-person-rule on authoritative governance + threat-model docs.
#
# CIRISVerify#54 (Fed TM §3.3 Gap G / §6.7 F-AV-MAINT): the threat
# model is markdown in a git repo with no signing requirement and no
# two-person rule. A maintainer compromise — or a careless edit — that
# silently downgrades an F-AV's `Status: Open` to `Status: Mitigated`,
# mis-specifies a RATCHET signal, or quietly weakens a mitigation,
# corrupts every downstream RATCHET designer's mental model. RATCHET
# cannot detect this (the threat model defines RATCHET's job); detection
# is external — review, signed-version verification, hash mismatch.
#
# This file is Phase 1 (the cheap structural half): require an explicit
# reviewer on every change to the authoritative docs. Pair it with a
# branch-protection rule ("Require review from Code Owners") on `main`.
# Phase 2 is the cryptographic half — `ciris_verify_core::doc_integrity`
# (hybrid-signed content hash). Phase 3 composes the M-of-N steward
# threshold (CIRISVerify#31) over the doc signature.

# Authoritative threat-model + governance documents — two-person rule.
